:: Forest Shop Lights 2
<<effects>><<npc Gwylan 1>><<person1>>

The room on the other side is pitch black. You take a step in, and immediately smell roses. You hear someone talking, but their voice sounds strange. It's like trying to remember a voice you haven't heard in years.
<br><br>

"...not my fault you led <<phim>> right to me!"
<br>
You hear a rumble at your feet. As if something deep below was trembling in protest.
<br>
"I don't usually need to lock the door! Excuse me for getting comfortable in my own home!"
<br>
Another rumble, pressing against your feet as you walk further into the blackness.
<br>
"That's <i>your</i> job. Can we please not fight? I think <<pshes>>—"
<br><br>

"Are you alright?" Now you recognise the voice. It's Gwylan. <<Hes>> standing right in front of you. At a counter. In the shop.
<br><br>

You're standing in the shop. It's normally lit, and the shelves are all in their usual place. You blink away the confusion. Gwylan looks at you with worry. "You've been standing there staring at me for a while." You still smell roses.
<br><br>

<<link [[Ask what just happened|Forest Shop Lights 3]]>><<set $phase to 1>><</link>>
