:: Forest Shop Nowhere
<<canvas-model-override "trauma" true>>
<<canvas-model-override "eyes_half" true>>
<<canvas-model-override "mouth" "cry">>
<<canvas-model-freeze "player">>
<<hallucinogen 10>>
You enter the forest shop, and immediately realise something is wrong. It's empty. Nobody.
<br><br>

Not just of its keeper. It's <i>entirely</i> empty. No shelves, no clothes, no strange mossy cabinets packed with knick-knacks. No light. Not even from the door behind you. It stops at the threshold.
<br><br>

No walls. No ceiling.
<br><br>

You take a step forward, and realise far too late that there's <span class="red">no air, either</span>. Your vision goes hazy in an instant, stars creeping into the edges of your vision as your muscles seize.
<br><br>

No hope. No safety. No life.
<br><br>

A pain overtakes your chest, spreading out from your heart. You look down, and see a <span class="tentacle">crackling scar</span> erupting from your skin in the same spot. <<pain 4>><<trauma 50>>
<br><br>

No glory. No pleasure. Damnation.
<br><br>

Something appears in the emptiness ahead. A pair of antlers, made of the same writhing nothingness as your scar. You collapse. There's no floor. You fall.
<br><br>

Nowhere.
<br><br>

<<link [[다음|Forest Shop Nowhere Passout]]>><<endevent>><<pass 15>><</link>>
