:: Forest Shop Nowhere Talk
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if $passoutReason is "hyperthermia">>
	<<set Weather.Temperature.override.increase.inside(-5, "A small fan keeps you cool.")>>
<<elseif $passoutReason is "hypothermia">>
	<<set Weather.Temperature.override.increase.inside(5, "A thick blanket keeps you warm.")>>
<</if>>
<<unset $passoutReason>>
<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("romance")>>
	<<set $gwylan.trouble to "silenced">>
	You open your mouth to speak as <<his>> finger trails up your neck. A faint blue mist exits and swirls in between Gwylan's fingers. <span class="red">You have been silenced.</span>
	<br><br>

	<<if $avery_mansion and $brownFoxCoverBlown>>
		"Shhh... no more screaming, my dear child. I can't bear to hear you sing for the elks again.
	<<else>>
		"Shhh... you needn't say anything, my dear child.
	<</if>>
	I already understand. It can be so, so very difficult to refuse the hand that feeds you, even when the same hand strikes you. Even when your body flinches by instinct."
	<<He>> lays down on top of you, forcing you to look into <<his>> eyes. "I'm sorry I wasn't there to protect you. I failed you. I won't fail again. I will protect you from the world..."
	<br><br>

	<<if $worn.neck.name is "familiar collar">>
		<<His>> hands caress your collar.
	<<else>>
		<<His>> hands place something around your neck with a click.
		<<if $worn.upper.cursed is 1>>
			<<set _neckRuinedHere to true>>
			<<set $worn.neck.type.push("broken")>>
			<<neckruined true>>
		<<elseif $worn.neck.name isnot "naked">>
			<<set _neckStrippedHere to true>>
			<<generalUndress "wardrobe" "neck">>
		<</if>>
		<<neckwear 40>>
	<</if>>
	<<He>> whispers something, and plants a kiss on your cheek. A brief flash of green highlights your faces.
	<<if !$hypnosis_traits.devotion>>
		<<gwylanHypnosis "devotion" 15>>
	<</if>>
	<br><br>

	<span class="red">"...but I must also protect the world from you."</span>
	<br><br>

	<<link [[다음|Forest Shop Taken Alt Start]]>><</link>>
	<br>
<<else>>
	<<switch $gwylan.trouble>>
		<<case "helpless">>
			<<if $gwylan.triumph is "innocent" and $innocencestate>>
				<<if $gwylan.wary gt 1>><<set $gwylan.wary-->><</if>>
				Gwylan scowls briefly, but seems to remember something. "You poor, naive child. You truly believe you're helpless, don't you?" <<He>> shakes <<his>> head. "Someone has taught you that helplessness. It is not who you are."
				<<He>> continues petting your hair, now looking almost protective of you. "We must break you out of this, or this world will chew you up."
			<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning") or ["spite", "survival", "revenge", "divine"].includes($gwylan.triumph)>>
				<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
				Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "Nonsense. You've merely forgotten how strong you are." <<He>> leans in. "I haven't. I still remember everything you've told me. You are far from helpless.
				Why do you lie to yourself? What has made your heart waver like this?" <<He>> shakes <<his>> head, lifting yours out of <<his>> lap and laying you down on the floor. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
				<br><br>

				<<if $avery_mansion?.fox?.known>>
					"Even if you were as weak and helpless as you're trying to make me believe, you had help. <span class="red">You denied it willingly.</span>" <<set $gwylan.wary++>>
				<</if>>
				<<He>> stands.
				<<switch $gwylan.triumph>>
					<<case "spite">>"You told me that spite is what kept you holding on. Did that spite simply vanish?"
					<<case "survival">>"The survival instincts you spoke of must be far off. The fox that plays dead is the first devoured."
					<<case "optimism">>"You spoke of a better future on the horizon. It just became so much further away."
					<<case "child">>"Helpless. How insulting to hear from someone that claimed to be holding on for <<pher>> child."
					<<case "children">>"Helpless. How insulting to hear from someone that claimed to be holding on for <<pher>> children."
					<<case "orphans" "kind">>"Helpless. How insulting to hear from someone that claimed to want to help others."
					<<case "special">>"You spoke of holding on for someone special. I think I know who you were talking about, now. You've made a terrible choice."
					<<case "Gwylan">>"Your words are just as empty as when you told me that I was the one you were holding on for." <<npcincr Gwylan dom -50>><<lllyearning>>
					<<case "revenge">>"Your desire for revenge must have been thoroughly erased."
					<<case "divine">>"The divine purpose you claimed to be your anchor must have rusted away. Where did your conviction go?"
					<<case "lust">>"You aren't just a toy to be used."
					<<case "innocent">>"There was an empty innocence behind your eyes, once. It's gone, now. Yet you hold on to this learned helplessness."
					<<case "curiosity">>"Your curiosity must have dulled."
					<<default>>"Letting yourself be thrashed by the tides is a sure way to be broken against the shore."
				<</switch>>
			<<else>>
				Gwylan continues to pet you. "You face powerful people. I understand. I wish I could keep you here and protect you from them, but we can't stay sheltered as the world outside burns."
			<</if>>
		<<case "fear">>
			<<switch $gwylan.triumph>>
				<<case "spite" "revenge" "divine">>
					<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
					Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "So your desire to uphold your own justice is gone, then. How tragic. Your teeth have been pulled."
					<<He>> shakes <<his>> head, lifting yours out of <<his>> lap and laying you down on the floor. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
				<<case "survival">>
					<<if $gwylan.wary gt 1>><<set $gwylan.wary-->><</if>>
					<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>><<His>> expression falters.<<else>><<He>> smiles sadly.<</if>> "You told me that survival comes before all else. You were just following your instincts, then."
					<<He>> looks down at <<his>> arms. "Anything it takes to survive. Even if one has to submit and take the beatings." <<npcincr Gwylan dom 5>><<gyearning>>
				<<case "child" "children" "orphans" "kind" "Gwylan">>
					<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
					Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "Fear? What of the fear that those you love will feel in this ever-darkening world?"
					<<He>> shakes <<his>> head, lifting yours out of <<his>> lap and laying you down on the floor. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
				<<case "special">>
					<<if isLoveInterest("Avery")>>
						<<if $gwylan.wary gt 1>><<set $gwylan.wary-->><</if>>
						<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>><<His>> expression falters.<<else>><<He>> smiles sadly.<</if>> "I understand. It can be so, so very difficult to refuse the hand that feeds you, even when the same hand strikes you.
						Even when your body flinches by instinct." <<He>> looks down at <<his>> arms. "Anything it takes to survive." <<npcincr Gwylan dom 5>><<gyearning>>
					<<else>>
						<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
						Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "Fear? What of the fear that those you love will feel in this ever-darkening world?"
						<<He>> shakes <<his>> head, lifting yours out of <<his>> lap and laying you down on the floor. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
					<</if>>
				<<case "curiosity">>
					<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
					Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "So your curiosity is only as deep as a puddle, unable to break through something as weak as fear. How troublesome."
					<<He>> shakes <<his>> head, lifting yours out of <<his>> lap and laying you down on the floor. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
				<<default>>
					<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
						<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
						Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "After all you've told me, something as weak as fear is enough to make you heel? What of the fear I felt, worrying whether the fool Elk-puppets swayed you?"
						<<He>> shakes <<his>> head, lifting yours out of <<his>> lap and laying you down on the floor. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
					<<else>>
						<<if $gwylan.wary gt 1>><<set $gwylan.wary-->><</if>>
						Gwylan pulls you up into a hug. "I understand. It can be so, so very difficult to refuse the hand that feeds you, even when the same hand strikes you.
						Even when your body flinches by instinct." <<He>> looks down at <<his>> hands behind you. "Anything it takes to survive." <<npcincr Gwylan dom 5>><<gyearning>>
					<</if>>
			<</switch>>
		<<case "pride">>
			<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
				<<if ["spite", "revenge"].includes($gwylan.triumph)>>
					A smile breaks through Gwylan's stern expression. "You told me you were spiteful, but I didn't expect it to go this deep.
				<<else>>
					<<He>> sighs, but continues to pet your head. "I hope you know how foolish that was.
				<</if>>
				It won't be worth it. Avery will drag us all down to Hell with <<nnpc_him "Avery">>, now.
				<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
					This is exactly what Landry and I were trying to prevent. Spite isn't worth condemning the world, and the chance to spur the fall has long since passed."
				<<else>>
					It's exactly what La—" <<He>> catches <<himself>>. "Spite isn't worth condemning the world."
				<</if>>
			<<else>>
				<<set $gwylan.wary += 2>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
				Gwylan scoffs. <span class="red"><<He>> looks disappointed.</span> "It's too late for that. When Avery falls, <<nnpc_He "Avery">>'ll be dragging us all down to Hell with <<nnpc_him "Avery">>.
				<<if $brownFoxRevealed>>
					It's exactly what Landry and I were trying to prevent, and you've fed right into it. Spite isn't worth condemning the world, and the chance to spur the fall has long since passed."
				<<else>>
					It's exactly what La—" <<He>> catches <<himself>>. "Spite isn't worth condemning the world."
				<</if>>
				<<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
				<br><br>

				<<He>> stands.
				<<switch $gwylan.triumph>>
					<<case "spite" "revenge">>"Ashes. That's all that will be left when your vision of deeper revenge is fulfilled."
					<<case "survival">>"The survival instincts you spoke of must be far off. The fox that plays dead is the first devoured."
					<<case "optimism">>"You spoke of a better future on the horizon. It just became so much further away."
					<<case "child">>"At this rate, your child won't have a world to grow up in."
					<<case "children">>"At this rate, your children won't have a world to grow up in."
					<<case "orphans" "kind" "special" "Gwylan">>"Those you love will suffer all the more thanks to your wish for a deeper revenge."
					<<case "divine">>"I should have known you'd miss the forest for the fire, just like the Cloister."
					<<case "lust">>"Your lust has turned to wrath."
					<<case "innocent">>"There was an empty innocence behind your eyes, once. It's gone, now. Perhaps it was a mistake to rid you of it."
					<<case "curiosity">>"This isn't morbid curiosity. This is lunacy."
					<<default>>"You were better off when you didn't know what you were holding on for."
				<</switch>>
			<</if>>
		<<case "damnation">>
			"The only way I can go is up. To step off the path is to fall," you say,
			<br><br>

			"You aren't the one rising, dear. You're the footstool." Gwylan stares down at you, expressionless. "Avery has tied a noose around <<nnpc_his 'Avery'>> own neck. You'll be kicked away and fall regardless.
			<<switch $gwylan.triumph>>
				<<case "spite" "revenge">>If this is your way of spiting those who hurt you, you're doing a poor job of it." <<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>><<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>><<set $gwylan.wary++>>
				<<case "survival">>You said to me that survival was above all, yet you yearn to join <<nnpc_him "Avery">> in that noose." <<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>><<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>><<set $gwylan.wary++>>
				<<case "optimism">>You spoke of a better future on the horizon. Have you already given up on that?" <<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>><<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>><<set $gwylan.wary++>>
				<<case "special">>Now you tell me you'll stare down from the floor, yearning to join <<nnpc_him "Avery">> in that same noose?" <<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>><<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>><<set $gwylan.wary++>>
				<<case "lust">>If you think it's too late to change course, you're wrong." <<He>> gives you a more patient smile.
				<<default>>You sound like a guilty initiate from the temple, determined to punish yourself far more than you deserve." <<He>> allows a softer smile to cross <<his>> face.
			<</switch>>
		<<case "sedition">>
			<<if $gwylan.triumph is "divine">>
				<<if $gwylan.wary gt 1>><<set $gwylan.wary-->><</if>>
				Gwylan lets out a long breath.
				<br><br>

				"Another soul betrayed by <<pher>> siblings, then."
				<<if $demon gte 6 or $fallenangel gte 2>>
					<<He>> frowns. "I can imagine what happened to make you turn against them."
				<<else>>
					<<He>> shakes <<his>> head. "I can't even be disappointed in you."
				<</if>>
				<<He>> continues petting your head. "I am no friend of the Cloister, but this is too much. It would be better to remove the poison they, too, are opposing. Still, I empathise with your desire to see them humbled."
			<<else>>
				<<if $gwylan.triumph is "lust">>
					<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
					Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "All for what, your desire for lust? I remember, dear. You fear they'll punish the hedonism that keeps you afloat in this sea of torment."
					<<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
				<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
					<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
					Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "A fool's errand. You know by now that the best way to oppose the Cloister would be to remove the reason they take such extreme measures."
					<<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
				<<else>>
					Gwylan sighs. "I understand, but the best way to oppose the Cloister would be to remove the reason they take such extreme measures."
				<</if>>
			<</if>>
		<<case "lust">>
			<<set $gwylan.wary += 3>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 2>>
			Gwylan stares down at you. <<He>> blinks, saying nothing, waiting for you to continue. You have nothing more to say.
			<br><br>

			<<if $gwylan.triumph is $gwylan.trouble and $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
				"So, what you told me that day holds true, but it's been twisted. Darkened." <<He>> holds <<his>> hand over your heart. "What happened to you? I want <<pcpetname "Gwylan" "my">> back."
			<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("partners")>>
				<<He>> looks wounded. "You have given me your heart, dear, and I know this is not its true rhythm."
				<<He>> then slaps you across the face. "You're being incredibly stupid. Give me back <<pcpetname "Gwylan" "my">>." <<He>> slaps you again. You can't even move to block it. <<pain 8>><<ggpain>>
			<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
				<<He>> then slaps you across the face. "You're being incredibly stupid. Give me back <<pcpetname "Gwylan" "my">>." <<He>> slaps you again. You can't even move to block it. <<pain 8>><<ggpain>>
			<<else>>
				"That's it?" <<He>> giggles. "That reason is so utterly mundane that I can't tell if you're serious. Is that all it would take for you to throw the world away?" <<He>> smiles. It makes you uncomfortable.
			<</if>>
			<br><br>

			<<switch $gwylan.triumph>>
				<<case "spite">>"You're becoming one of them."
				<<case "survival">>"You spoke to me of survival above all else. You're laying down in the road, dear."
				<<case "optimism">>"You spoke of a better future on the horizon. Now you've turned, and are running away from it."
				<<case "child">>"You told me you were holding on for your child. What happened? Is this world no longer worthy of you?"
				<<case "children">>"You told me you were holding on for your children. What happened? Is this world no longer worthy of you?"
				<<case "orphans" "kind">>"How insulting to hear from someone that claimed to want to help others. You're dooming them all."
				<<case "special">>"You spoke of holding on for someone special. I think I know who you were talking about, now. You've made a terrible choice."
				<<case "Gwylan">>"You've lost yourself."
				<<case "revenge">>"Your desire for revenge must have been twisted."
				<<case "divine">>"The divine purpose you claimed to be your anchor must have rusted away. Where did your conviction go?"
				<<case "lust">>"Pleasure is temporary. This path will leave you empty."
				<<case "innocent">>"There was an empty innocence behind your eyes, once. It's gone, now."
				<<case "curiosity">>"This isn't morbid curiosity. this is lunacy."
				<<default>>
			<</switch>>
			<<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the floor. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
		<<case "spite">>
			<<set $gwylan.wary += 1>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 2>>
			<<switch $speech_attitude>>
				<<case "meek">>"Everyone has hurt me. I can't trust anybody. I have to go where I'm dragged to keep the pain away, and do what I can to hurt them back."
				<<case "bratty">>"A world as rotten as this isn't worth it. I'll drag everyone down to hell with me."
				<<default>>"I've been wronged and hurt. I know this will hurt them all back."
			<</switch>>
			<br><br>

			Gwylan stares down at you. <<He>> blinks, saying nothing, waiting for you to continue. You have nothing more to say. <<He>> smiles sadly. "You sound like Bailey." <<trauma 24>><<ggtrauma>>
			<br><br>

			<<He>> lifts your head, and props you up against the side of a wardrobe. "Tell me. Do you think me naive? Idealistic? Do you think my concern for you to be disingenuous? Do you think I've used you?"
			<<He>> opens the wardrobe, and starts fishing through it. "Is the world not worth helping for just one friend who understands? For one rose in the muck?" <<He>> pulls something out harshly.
			"Or do you simply want to pluck it? Do you think that's mercy?"
			<br><br>

			<span class="pink">You see <<his>> clothes drop around the corner of the wardrobe.</span> "You've told me so much. Please don't pretend that I don't understand." <<He>> chuckles. "Because I used to think exactly like you do."
			<br><br>

			<<He>> walks around the corner, <<his>> back facing you. <span class="red"><<Hes>> covered in dozens, possibly hundreds, of scars. Wounds you somehow missed despite seeing <<him>> naked before. Cuts. Scratches. Bites. Burns.</span>
			<br><br>

			As you stare, they seem to move, blur, and hide themselves, like a shifting canvas of torture. Older wounds fight to reach the surface of <<his>> skin. Each configuration paints a lifetime of suffering on <<his>> body.
			Finally, <<his>> skin clears of wounds, only for two much larger ones to rip down <<his>> back at <<his>> shoulder blades. <<He>> turns around and crouches down to your level, placing a finger over your heart.
			"You're not the only one with an invisible wound, dear. I understand more than you could possibly imagine." <<He>> puts <<his>> other hand on your cheek. "You are not alone."
		<<case "Bailey">>
			<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
				"Helping Avery will make Bailey regret selling me," you say. "Maybe it will send a message."
			<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
				"Bailey seems to hate Avery, so helping Avery will hurt Bailey. That's all I care about."
			<<else>>
				"Bailey sold me," you say. "It's <<nnpc_his "Bailey">> fault. Helping Avery will hurt <<nnpc_him "Bailey">>."
			<</if>>
			<br><br>

			<<if $gwylan.triumph is "orphans">>
				<<He>> sighs. "I understand. The orphans are important to you, it's not just your own interests you're looking out for. Still, these are far worse people than Bailey you're getting mixed up with, dear.
				I can't say I don't understand, though." <<He>> continues petting your head. "It's a rotten thing, to be forced to put a personal struggle aside for the sake of the world. I understand. I understand more than you know."
			<<elseif ["child", "children"].includes($gwylan.triumph)>>
				<<He>> sighs. "I understand. You can't stand having your <<= $gwylan.triumph is "child" ? "child" : "children">> stuck under <<nnpc_his "Bailey">> care. Still, these are far worse people than Bailey you're getting mixed up with, dear.
				I can't say I don't understand, though." <<He>> continues petting your head. "It's a rotten thing, to be forced to put a personal struggle aside for the sake of the world. I understand. I understand more than you know."
			<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
				<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
				Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "You know by now that there are bigger threats than Bailey."
				<<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
			<<else>>
				"These are far worse people than Bailey you're getting mixed up with, dear. I can't say I don't understand, though. Bailey is the root of all your personal struggles, no?"
				<<He>> continues petting your head. "It's a rotten thing, to be forced to put a personal struggle aside for the sake of the world. I understand. I understand more than you know."
			<</if>>
		<<case "Landry">>
			<<if $speech_attitude is "meek">>
				"Landry was so confusing when <<nnpc_he "Landry">> proposed this," you say. "I didn't want to hurt anyone."
			<<elseif $speech_attitude is "bratty">>
				"Landry was far too suspicious about it," you say. "I didn't want to play <<nnpc_his "Landry">> game and get someone hurt."
			<<else>>
				"Landry wasn't clear enough," you say. "<<nnpc_He "Landry">> was hiding something. I didn't want anyone getting hurt."
			<</if>>
			<br><br>

			<<if $gwylan.triumph is "kind">>
				<<He>> frowns. "Landry hides much. Someone as kindhearted as you couldn't understand the darkness bubbling up under the surface of this conflict. It's a terrible choice to have to make."
			<<elseif $gwylanSeen.includes("yearning")>>
				<<set $gwylan.wary++>><<set _gwylanDisappointed to 1>>
				Gwylan frowns, <span class="red">looking disappointed</span>. "You know the stakes. You know that the world can't become clean without us getting dirty."
				<<He>> lifts your head and lays you flat on the ground. <<npcincr Gwylan dom -25>><<llyearning>>
			<<else>>
				<<He>> sighs, and allows <<himself>> a small giggle. "<<nnpc_He "Landry">> hasn't been fully honest with me, either. I can imagine how shady <<nnpc_his "Landry">> proposal sounded."
			<</if>>
		<<case "Harper">>
			You forget your words as soon as they leave your mouth.
			<br><br>

			Gwylan looks at you with concern. "I am begging you to let me remove that <<nnpc_gender "Harper">>'s influence from your mind. <<nnpc_Hes "Harper">> using you as a tool, and <<nnpc_he "Harper">> will discard you as soon as your edges dull.
			If there is true evil in the world, it answers to <<nnpc_him "Harper">>."
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<if _gwylanDisappointed gte 1>>
		<<He>> looks down to your bandages again.
	<<else>>
		<<His>> head tilts back and forth, as if <<hes>> trying to see every part of you. Then, <<his>> eyes lock on the bandages.
	<</if>>
	"Forgive me, but I've already taken precautions while you were unconscious. Your wound shouldn't flare up from my mere presence anymore."
	<<if _gwylanDisappointed is 2>>
		<<set $daily.gwylan.locked to true>>
		<<His>> hands open and close at <<his>> sides. "This is not your truest heart. You wouldn't dare enter my forest again if that was how you really felt."
		<<He>> produces a red phial, opens it, and holds it under your nose. <span class="green">The weight lifts from your limbs.</span>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> helps you stand, and hugs you. "I'd like to be alone for today.
		<<if $gwylanSeen.includes("partners")>>
			Look at me. Hey. Look at me." <<He>> turns your head to look into <<his>> eyes. "I won't abandon you, no matter how much you lash out at the world." <<He>> gives you a peck on the lips.
		<<else>>
			I hope you return soon, though. There's much work to be done. I've made terrible mistakes of my own. Some worse than this."
		<</if>>
		<<His>> words sink deep into you, and you find yourself returning the embrace. <<trauma -12>><<lltrauma>>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> leads you outside.
		<br><br>

		<<link [[다음|Forest]]>><<clotheson>><<endevent>><<set $eventskip to 1>><<set $forest to 0>><</link>>
		<br>
	<<elseif _gwylanDisappointed is 1>>
		<<He>> kneels down, producing a red phial. <<He>> opens it and holds it under your nose. <span class="green">The weight lifts from your limbs.</span>
		<br><br>

		<<He>> helps you stand, and hugs you. "Do not betray yourself. The world is cruel, but beautiful. Nothing, and I truly do mean nothing, is worth aligning yourself with the servants of the Elk.
		A single mistake does not mean you deserve a spiral of damnation. I've made terrible mistakes of my own. Some worse than this."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> pulls away, and steps behind <<his>> usual counter.
		<br><br>

		<<link [[다음|Forest Shop Entrance]]>><<clotheson>><<endevent>><</link>>
		<br>
	<<else>>
		<<He>> pulls you into a hug. "There's much work to be done. Even if you've made a terrible mistake, I'd rather have you by my side. I've made terrible mistakes of my own in the past. Some worse than this."
		<br><br>

		<<He>> helps you stand, and steps behind <<his>> usual counter.
		<br><br>

		<<link [[다음|Forest Shop Entrance]]>><<clotheson>><<endevent>><</link>>
		<br>
	<</if>>
<</if>>

:: Forest Shop Nowhere Talk Forever
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<span class="red"><<He>> freezes, looking down at you in horror.</span>
<br><br>

"No. No, no no no. You can't become like me, dear. You don't understand what this is like. Nobody is worth this." More black tears start to run down <<his>> face.
<span class="purple"><<He>> changes again. <<He>> pulls <<his>> hands away from you as they become gnarled and blackened.</span>
<br><br>

"A memory with no name. A heart that can't love without threat of bursting open. Hands that can't embrace without tearing to bloody ribbons. A body that can never know true parenthood.
An identity in shreds. Nameless. Hopeless. Erased. And the antlers. Forever splitting, fracturing, rupturing." <<He>> clutches <<his>> head.
<br><br>

<<if $demon gte 6>>
	"Do you think you've reached the bottom? Do you believe these little wings and horns of yours have sealed your damnation? You've barely breached the surface. This..."
	<span class="red"><<His>> misshapen claws slowly rake fresh cuts into <<his>> body.</span> "This is what Hell really looks like, my little imp. I can't let you reach these depths. It would tear me apart."
	<span class="red">Black ichor trails down <<his>> skin. <<He>> runs a claw down your face, leaving some of it on you, too.</span>
	<br><br>
<</if>>

<span class="blue">You muster all your willpower, and manage to move your left arm.</span> You shakily place your hand against <<his>> chest and smile. "Nobody <i>is</i> worth this," you say. Your arm falls back to your side.
<br><br>

<<His>> pupils become pinpricks. "I'm sorry. I'm so sorry. It never should have come to this. It's all my fault."
<<He>> steadies <<himself>>, wiping away <<his>> tears. "I'll take responsibility. I'll keep you safe from these delusions. I'll protect you from the world..."
<br><br>

<<if $worn.neck.name is "familiar collar">>
	<<His>> hands caress your collar.
<<else>>
	<<His>> hands place something around your neck with a click.
	<<if $worn.upper.cursed is 1>>
		<<set _neckRuinedHere to true>>
		<<set $worn.neck.type.push("broken")>>
		<<neckruined true>>
	<<elseif $worn.neck.name isnot "naked">>
		<<set _neckStrippedHere to true>>
		<<generalUndress "wardrobe" "neck">>
	<</if>>
	<<neckwear 40>>
<</if>>
<<He>> whispers something, and plants a kiss on your cheek. A brief flash of green highlights your faces.
<<if !$hypnosis_traits.devotion>>
	<<gwylanHypnosis "devotion" 15>>
<</if>>
<br><br>

<span class="red">"...but I must also protect the world from you."</span>
<br><br>

<<link [[다음|Forest Shop Taken Alt Start]]>><</link>>
<br>

:: Forest Shop Taken Alt Start
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $worn.neck.cursed to 1>>
<<if !$worn.neck.type.includes("leash")>>
	<<set $worn.neck.type.push("leash")>>
<</if>>
<<set $gwylan.wary to 1>>
<<set $gwylan.timer.lastSeen to Time.date.timeStamp>>
<<He>> lifts <<his>> hand. A ribbon of green light connects it with the collar around your neck.
<br><br>

"I can not trust that your will is your own. Forgive me, but it must be..." <<he>> leans down and kisses you. <<gwylanKiss>>
<br><br>

<<He>> withdraws. "...suppressed. Your collar will ensure the hypnosis remains in place <span class="red">indefinitely</span>." <<He>> smiles, but it doesn't reach <<his>> ears. "I hope you find it comfortable. I made it just for you." <<He>> flips up the golden heart-shaped plate.
It has your name engraved on it. <<Hes>> right. It is comfortable. So comfortable that your muscles can't help but relax.
<br><br>

Your mind fills with terrifying submission. You don't want to resist anymore, and it scares you. Your head then throbs, as if the thought of fearing Gwylan was heresy.
<br><br>

<<hypnosisText "You lay still as <<he>> leans in for another kiss.">> <<His>> emerald eyes, wide open, overtake your vision.
<br>

<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion lt 5>>
	<br>
	<<gwylanHypnosis "devotion" 25>><br>You slip further.
<</if>>
<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion lt 5>>
	<<gwylanHypnosis "devotion" 25>><br>Further.
<</if>>
<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion lt 5>>
	<<gwylanHypnosis "devotion" 25>><br>Yet further.
<</if>>
<<if $hypnosis_traits.devotion lt 5>>
	<<gwylanHypnosis "devotion" 25>><br>It's beautiful.
<</if>>
<br>

You feel something leave you, alongside <<his>> tongue. Gwylan has taken something from you. The thought doesn't scare you anymore, though.
<<hypnosisText "<<He>> knows what's best for you. This is all for your sake.">>
<br><br>

<<He>> smiles. "You'll stay here with me." <<He>> tugs your collar. "Forever. It's the only way to keep everyone safe. It's what we promised each other, my love. And no promise for or against me has ever been broken."
<<He>> lays down beside you again, his eyes still staring into yours. "I love you."
<br><br>

<<He>> snaps <<his>> fingers, and you fall asleep. You know you won't wake up as the same person.
<br><br>

<<hypnosisText "<span class='red'>But you don't mind.</span>">>
<br><br>

