:: Forest Shop Charms
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<if !$gwylanSeen.includes("sample")>>
	You examine the strips of cloth. They're decorated with strange branching patterns. Most are the same size, but one is significantly larger than the rest, around the size of a small rug.
	<br><br>

	Many of them are blackened and burnt near the bottom.
	<<if $world_corruption_hard gte 1>>
		<<set _charmsCorrupted to Math.ceil($world_corruption_hard / 2)>>
		<span class="purple"><<Number _charmsCorrupted>></span> of the smaller ones <<pluralise _charmsCorrupted "is">> <span class="purple">stained purple</span>. Some of the others might be too, but it's hard to tell with how damaged they are.
	<<else>>
		You don't notice anything unusual about them, though. <span class="green">This fills you with a strange comfort.</span>
	<</if>>

	<<if ["shop", "garden"].includes(gwylanSchedule()) and !$gwylanSeen.includes("charms") and !$gwylan.timer.eventShopEnd>>
		<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("charms")>>
		<<npc Gwylan>><<person1>>
		<br><br>

		"Don't worry about those." Gwylan's voice comes from right behind you, making you jump. "Just some old decorations. They're not for sale." <<He>> steps back into the gloom as quickly as <<he>> arrived.
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	You examine the measuring charms.
	<br><br>

	<<if $world_corruption_hard gte 1>>
		<span class="purple"><<Number $world_corruption_hard>></span> of the small charms <<pluralise $world_corruption_hard "is">> <span class="purple">stained purple</span>.
		A faint mist leaks from <<pluralise $world_corruption_hard "it">>, into the larger charm at the center.
	<<else>>
		<span class="green">None of the small charms have stained purple.</span>
	<</if>>

	You look closer at the larger charm. On both the left and right sides of it, ten black lines have been sewn in at even intervals.
	<<if $world_corruption_soft is 0>>
