:: Forest Shop Wraith Talk 2
<<effects>><<run statusCheck("Gwylan")>>
<<set $gwylanSeen.pushUnique("bloodmoon")>>
<<if $phase is "thief">>
	<<switch $speech_attitude>>
		<<case "meek">>"I stole something I shouldn't have, and now it won't leave me alone," you say.
		<<case "bratty">>"I took a stupid necklace, and it hasn't left me alone since," you say.
		<<default>>"I think I took something important from it," you say. "A necklace."
	<</switch>>
	<br><br>

	<<He>> covers <<his>> mouth. "Oh, <<pcpetname "Gwylan">>. I doubt I need to tell you how bad that is."
<<elseif $phase is "diver">>
	"I funded Winter's field office at the lake," you say. "That drew a lot of attention to it."
	<br><br>

	<<Hes>> silent for a long moment. "It could be worse. A lot worse."
<<elseif $phase is "unknown">>
	"I don't know what it wants with me," you say.
	<br><br>

	<<He>> nods. "Not surprising, it's quite the enigmatic entity."
<<else>>
	You stay silent. Gwylan frowns. "I know it's scary, but you're safe now."
<</if>>
<br><br>

<<He>> stands back up. "Names have power, so one must be cautious when referring to it. Although, even were its true name remembered, I don't think anyone could speak it aloud."
<br><br>

<<He>> touches the wall of the shop. "One safe title for it is the <span class="purple">Ivory Wraith</span>. It's impersonal enough to not grant it any additional presence. The name stuck amidst the more eccentric. The cryptid-obsessed types."
<br><br>

You lean forward a little. "What exactly is it?"
<br><br>

<<He>> puts a hand to <<his>> chin. "Well, if you believe the myths, a wraith is typically someone who died recently, or a premonition of someone that will die soon. The Ivory one is an old, old soul, though.
It shows up in tales dating back to the middle ages, if not earlier. There's another definition of that word that could fit, that being someone reduced to a pale, thin shadow of their former self." <<He>> starts pacing.
<br><br>

"It doesn't neatly fit into any category of spirit or apparition. It wails like a banshee, but its gender is always inconsistent or indiscernible, and banshees are typically said to be related to the earth, not water.
<<if $wraith.state is "haunt">>It's vengeful like a revenant, and has the red eyes to match.<</if>> It shares some aspects with tales of guardian spirits, and even reminds me of some water spirits from cultures across the sea.
I think it's something wholly unique." <<He>> almost sounds excited. "I'd give it a new name myself, but that would make it stronger."
<br><br>

"It seemed to know you," you say.
<br><br>

<<He>> looks back to you. "We've shared this forest a long time. More importantly, if it can touch you, it must have some form of attachment to you. On nights like tonight, do yourself a favour and don't sleep.
I always stay awake during the blood moon, so you're welcome to stay here a while."
<br><br>

<<if _gwylanStatus.includes("badEndReady")>>
	As <<he>> finishes <<his>> words, you find your vision blurring. "In fact, I must insist." <<He>> giggles.
	<br><br>

	You fall out of your seat, but <<he>> catches you.
	<br><br>

	<<if _gwylanStatus.includes("aurigaScarConfront")>>
		<<link [[Everything fades to black...|Forest Shop Nowhere Passout]]>><<pass 30>><<endevent>><</link>>
	<<else>>
		<<link [[Everything fades to black...|Forest Shop Taken Start]]>><<pass 30>><<endevent>><</link>>
	<</if>>
<<else>>
	<<He>> returns to the gloom.
	<br><br>

	<<link [[다음|Forest Shop Entrance]]>><<endevent>><</link>>
	<br>
<</if>>

